_

_testAllCellsConnected(Maze) - Method in class generation.MazeFactoryTest
Verify that every cell has a path to the exit by verifying that for every cell c, there is at least one neighbor n of c that satisfies: |distance(c) - distance(n)|=1 c and n are not separated by a wallboard.
_testCells(MazeBuilderEller) - Method in class generation.MazeFactoryTestEller
Checks that all cells in the maze belong to the set with id=1, as prescribed by this implementation of Eller's algorithm.
_testCellSets(MazeBuilderEller) - Method in class generation.MazeFactoryTestEller
Checks that there is only one set of cells identified in the maze, that the id of this set is 1, and that all cells in the maze are contained in this set.
_testExitAtExpectedLocationByBorders(Maze) - Method in class generation.MazeFactoryTest
Get the exit cell identified by MazeFactoryTest.getMazeExitsByBorders(Maze) and compare it with the cell returned by Maze.getMazedists().getExitPosition()
_testExitAtExpectedLocationByDistance(Maze) - Method in class generation.MazeFactoryTest
Get the exit cell identified by MazeFactoryTest.getMazeExitsByDistance(Maze) and compare it with the cell returned by Maze.getMazedists().getExitPosition()
_testNoRoomsInPerfectMaze() - Method in class generation.MazeFactoryTest
Iterates over every cell in a perfect maze and confirms that the cell is not in a room (uses Floorplan.isInRoom(int x, int y)).
